    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-05-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="238"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d238">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.512 Stamp Tax/11</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Merrell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-18">May 18,
                            1929</date>.<lb/>[Received May 29.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 891</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the Department’s telegram No.
                    25 of March 27, 7 P.M. and to the last paragraph of the Legation’s despatch No.
                    871 of April 29, 1929, I have the honor to transmit herewith a copy and
                    translation of a reply<note n="7" xml:id="d238fn7">Not printed.</note> to the
                    Legation’s note making representations relative to the deposit of $50,000
                    required of foreign insurance companies doing business in Honduras by Decree 107
                    of April 1, 1922. As the Department will note this reply states that
                    instructions have been given to the appropriate Honduran authorities not to
                    require the deposit in question of American insurance companies or their
                    representatives in Honduras.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George R. Merrell, Jr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
